1) Mongo-Express Application (Manual using Docker commands)
🔹 Step 0: Create Custom Network

Command:

docker network create mongo-network

Description:
Creates a custom Docker network so containers can communicate securely using names instead of IPs.

🔹 A. Run MongoDB Container

Command:

docker run -d \
--name mongodb \
--network mongo-network \
-p 27017:27017 \
-e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME=admin \
-e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD=admin \
mongo

Description:

Runs MongoDB container in detached mode
Sets username & password for security
Maps port 27017 (database access)
Connects to custom network mongo-network
🔹 B. Run Mongo-Express Container

Command:

docker run -d \
--name mongo-express \
--network mongo-network \
-p 8081:8081 \
-e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINUSERNAME=admin \
-e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINPASSWORD=admin \
-e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_SERVER=mongodb \
mongo-express

Description:

Runs Mongo-Express GUI container
Connects to same network (mongo-network)
Uses container name mongodb as server
Maps port 8081 for browser access
🌐 Access in Browser:
http://localhost:8081

👉 This works because:

Both containers are on same network
Mongo-Express connects using container name (mongodb)
Port 8081 is exposed to host
✅ 2) Mongo-Express Application (Using Docker Compose)
🔹 docker-compose.yml

Create a file named docker-compose.yml

version: '3.8'

services:
  mongodb:
    image: mongo
    container_name: mongodb
    ports:
      - "27017:27017"
    environment:
      MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME: admin
      MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD: admin

  mongo-express:
    image: mongo-express
    container_name: mongo-express
    ports:
      - "8081:8081"
    environment:
      ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINUSERNAME: admin
      ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINPASSWORD: admin
      ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_SERVER: mongodb
    depends_on:
      - mongodb
🔹 Run Compose

Command:

docker-compose up -d

Description:

Starts both MongoDB and Mongo-Express together
Automatically creates a default network
Handles dependency (Mongo starts first)
🌐 Access Application:
http://localhost:8081
🔥 Key Concepts (Important for Viva)
🔹 Networking
Custom network → containers communicate using names
No need to use IP addresses
🔹 Environment Variables
Used to configure database credentials securely
🔹 Port Mapping
host_port:container_port
Example: 8081:8081
🔹 Docker Compose Benefits
One file for entire setup
Easy to share & reuse
One command deployment
💡 Extra (Best Practice - Volume)

If examiner asks, add volume:

volumes:
  - mongo-data:/data/db

volumes:
  mongo-data:

👉 Prevents data loss when container stops.
